---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Explore Differently — Christina Pham" description="A multi-channel brand campaign for a modern travel media company">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-meta reveal">
      <span>Campaign / Art Direction / Digital</span>
      <span>2025</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="reveal">Explore Differently</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub reveal">A multi-channel brand campaign repositioning a modern travel media company as a cultural discovery platform for Gen Z.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="hero-image reveal">
    <div class="hero-placeholder">
      <span class="hero-tagline">See what others walk past.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="overview">
    <div class="overview-grid">
      <div class="overview-details reveal">
        <div class="detail-item">
          <h3>Client</h3>
          <p>Modern Travel Media Co.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-item">
          <h3>Role</h3>
          <p>Visual Designer, Art Director</p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-item">
          <h3>Scope</h3>
          <p>Brand Campaign, Social, Email, Web, Pitch Deck</p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-item">
          <h3>Timeline</h3>
          <p>8 Weeks</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="overview-text reveal">
        <p>The travel content space is saturated with generic top-10 lists and influencer-driven itineraries. Young travelers — Gen Z and early-career professionals — are looking for something deeper: perspective, story, and a reason to slow down.</p>
        <p>Explore Differently is a multi-channel campaign that repositions the brand from a traditional travel guide into a cultural discovery platform — shifting the conversation from <em>where to go</em> to <em>how to see</em>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem & Insight -->
  <section class="problem-insight">
    <div class="pi-grid">
      <div class="pi-block reveal">
        <h2>The Problem</h2>
        <p>Young travelers are drowning in surface-level content. The dominant travel brands still communicate like guidebooks — transactional, list-based, and forgettable. There's a disconnect between how this audience actually travels and how brands talk to them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pi-block reveal">
        <h2>The Insight</h2>
        <p>Gen Z doesn't want to be told where to go. They want to be shown how to see. The most memorable travel moments aren't landmarks — they're the unexpected details: a conversation with a stranger, a side street that wasn't on the map, the way light hits a building at 6pm.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Strategy -->
  <section class="strategy">
    <div class="section-label reveal">
      <span>Strategy</span>
      <span class="label-line"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="strategy-content reveal">
      <h2>Reposition the brand as a platform for perspective, not just destinations.</h2>
      <p>The campaign celebrates the art of noticing — encouraging travelers to slow down, look closer, and discover what most people walk past. Every touchpoint reinforces this philosophy through editorial craft and a film-inspired visual language.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillars reveal-stagger">
      <div class="pillar reveal">
        <span class="pillar-num">01</span>
        <h3>Perspective</h3>
        <p>Content that teaches you how to see a place, not just visit it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar reveal">
        <span class="pillar-num">02</span>
        <h3>Story</h3>
        <p>Real narratives from real travelers, told with editorial craft and visual intention.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar reveal">
        <span class="pillar-num">03</span>
        <h3>Community</h3>
        <p>A movement of curious, intentional travelers who value depth over distance.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tagline -->
  <section class="tagline-section reveal">
    <blockquote>
      <p>"See what others walk past."</p>
    </blockquote>
  </section>

  <!-- Campaign Messages -->
  <section class="messages">
    <div class="section-label reveal">
      <span>Campaign Messages</span>
      <span class="label-line"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="messages-grid reveal-stagger">
      <div class="message reveal">
        <p>"Every corner has a story. Most people just walk by."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="message reveal">
        <p>"The best discoveries aren't on the map."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="message reveal">
        <p>"Travel is a practice. Not a checklist."</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Visual System -->
  <section class="visual-system">
    <div class="section-label reveal">
      <span>Visual System</span>
      <span class="label-line"></span>
    </div>

    <div class="system-intro reveal">
      <p>The visual identity draws from documentary photography and editorial print design. A muted, film-inspired palette grounds the campaign in warmth and authenticity, while the serif/sans typography pairing creates an elevated, magazine-quality feel across all touchpoints.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Color Palette -->
    <div class="palette reveal">
      <h3>Color Palette</h3>
      <div class="swatches">
        <div class="swatch">
          <div class="swatch-color" style="background: #1C1C1C;"></div>
          <span class="swatch-name">Ink</span>
          <span class="swatch-hex">#1C1C1C</span>
        </div>
        <div class="swatch">
          <div class="swatch-color" style="background: #F0EDE5;"></div>
          <span class="swatch-name">Parchment</span>
          <span class="swatch-hex">#F0EDE5</span>
        </div>
        <div class="swatch">
          <div class="swatch-color" style="background: #C4654A;"></div>
          <span class="swatch-name">Terracotta</span>
          <span class="swatch-hex">#C4654A</span>
        </div>
        <div class="swatch">
          <div class="swatch-color" style="background: #7D8E6E;"></div>
          <span class="swatch-name">Sage</span>
          <span class="swatch-hex">#7D8E6E</span>
        </div>
        <div class="swatch">
          <div class="swatch-color" style="background: #B5A99A;"></div>
          <span class="swatch-name">Stone</span>
          <span class="swatch-hex">#B5A99A</span>
        </div>
        <div class="swatch">
          <div class="swatch-color" style="background: #D8D4CC;"></div>
          <span class="swatch-name">Mist</span>
          <span class="swatch-hex">#D8D4CC</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Typography -->
    <div class="type-system reveal">
      <h3>Typography</h3>
      <div class="type-grid">
        <div class="type-sample type-display">
          <span class="type-label">Display — Instrument Serif</span>
          <p class="type-specimen-serif">The world rewards the curious.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="type-sample type-body">
          <span class="type-label">Body — Inter</span>
          <p class="type-specimen-sans">Every place has layers — history, rhythm, texture — that most visitors never notice. This campaign is about peeling them back. Clean, legible, and purposefully understated.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Image Direction -->
    <div class="image-direction reveal">
      <h3>Image Direction</h3>
      <div class="direction-grid">
        <div class="direction-block" style="background: #B5A99A;">
          <span>Film grain</span>
        </div>
        <div class="direction-block" style="background: #7D8E6E;">
          <span>Natural light</span>
        </div>
        <div class="direction-block tall" style="background: #C4654A;">
          <span>Documentary candid</span>
        </div>
        <div class="direction-block" style="background: #D8D4CC;">
          <span>Environmental detail</span>
        </div>
        <div class="direction-block" style="background: #1C1C1C; color: #F0EDE5;">
          <span>Muted palette</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Execution: Social -->
  <section class="execution">
    <div class="section-label reveal">
      <span>Execution — Instagram Campaign</span>
      <span class="label-line"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="exec-intro reveal">
      <p>Six posts alternating between type-forward compositions and full-bleed photography, plus a 5-slide carousel. Each post pairs strong typographic hierarchy with film-inspired imagery to create a cohesive editorial feed.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="social-grid reveal-stagger">
      <div class="social-post post-type reveal" style="background: #1C1C1C; color: #F0EDE5;">
        <span class="post-category">Type-Forward</span>
        <p class="post-headline">See what<br/>others<br/><em>walk past.</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="social-post post-image reveal" style="background: #B5A99A;">
        <span class="post-category" style="color: #1C1C1C;">Image-Dominant</span>
      </div>
      <div class="social-post post-quote reveal" style="background: #F0EDE5; color: #1C1C1C;">
        <span class="post-category">Pull Quote</span>
        <p class="post-quote-text">"Every corner<br/>has a story."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="social-post post-type reveal" style="background: #C4654A; color: #F0EDE5;">
        <span class="post-category" style="color: rgba(240,237,229,0.6);">Type-Forward</span>
        <p class="post-headline">Travel is<br/>a practice.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="social-post post-image reveal" style="background: #7D8E6E;">
        <span class="post-category" style="color: #F0EDE5;">Image-Dominant</span>
      </div>
      <div class="social-post post-type reveal" style="background: #F0EDE5; color: #1C1C1C; border: 1px solid #D8D4CC;">
        <span class="post-category">Carousel Cover</span>
        <p class="post-headline" style="font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2vw, 1.6rem);">5 Ways to<br/>See a City</p>
        <span class="post-swipe">Swipe →</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Execution: Email -->
  <section class="execution">
    <div class="section-label reveal">
      <span>Execution — Email Design</span>
      <span class="label-line"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="email-mockup reveal">
      <div class="email-frame">
        <div class="email-header">
          <span class="email-brand">Explore Differently</span>
          <span class="email-date">Issue 01 — April 2025</span>
        </div>
        <div class="email-hero" style="background: #B5A99A;">
          <p class="email-hero-text">The Art of<br/>Arriving Slowly</p>
        </div>
        <div class="email-body">
          <p class="email-intro">There's a moment, just after you step off the train in a new city, where everything is unfamiliar. The light, the rhythm of the street, the sound of a language you half-understand. That moment — before you check the map — is the trip.</p>
          <div class="email-divider"></div>
          <p class="email-section-label">Featured Story</p>
          <div class="email-story">
            <div class="email-story-image" style="background: #7D8E6E;"></div>
            <div class="email-story-text">
              <h4>Three Days in Lisbon Without a Plan</h4>
              <p>What happens when you stop following the guide.</p>
              <a href="#">Read the story →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Execution: Landing Page -->
  <section class="execution">
    <div class="section-label reveal">
      <span>Execution — Landing Page</span>
      <span class="label-line"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="exec-intro reveal">
      <p>An editorial-style landing page built around a vertical scroll experience. The hero uses subtle parallax on the background image, with content sections fading in as the user scrolls. Typography drives the hierarchy, with photography serving as atmospheric texture rather than decoration.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="landing-mockup reveal">
      <div class="landing-frame">
        <div class="landing-nav">
          <span>Explore Differently</span>
          <span>Menu</span>
        </div>
        <div class="landing-hero-section" style="background: #1C1C1C; color: #F0EDE5;">
          <p class="landing-overline">A new way to travel</p>
          <h2>See what others<br/><em>walk past.</em></h2>
          <p class="landing-hero-sub">Stories, perspectives, and places worth slowing down for.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="landing-content">
          <div class="landing-philosophy">
            <div class="landing-text">
              <p class="landing-section-label">The Philosophy</p>
              <h3>Travel isn't about destinations. It's about perspectives.</h3>
              <p>We believe the best trips aren't measured in miles. They're measured in moments of genuine discovery — the things you notice when you stop trying to see everything.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="landing-img" style="background: #C4654A;"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="landing-stories">
            <p class="landing-section-label">Featured Stories</p>
            <div class="landing-cards">
              <div class="landing-card">
                <div class="landing-card-img" style="background: #7D8E6E;"></div>
                <span>Lisbon</span>
              </div>
              <div class="landing-card">
                <div class="landing-card-img" style="background: #B5A99A;"></div>
                <span>Oaxaca</span>
              </div>
              <div class="landing-card">
                <div class="landing-card-img" style="background: #D8D4CC;"></div>
                <span>Kyoto</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Execution: Pitch Deck -->
  <section class="execution">
    <div class="section-label reveal">
      <span>Execution — Pitch Deck</span>
      <span class="label-line"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="deck-grid reveal-stagger">
      <div class="deck-slide reveal" style="background: #1C1C1C; color: #F0EDE5;">
        <div class="slide-content">
          <p class="slide-overline">Explore Differently</p>
          <h3>See what others<br/><em>walk past.</em></h3>
          <p class="slide-caption">Campaign Proposal — 2025</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="deck-slide reveal" style="background: #F0EDE5; color: #1C1C1C;">
        <div class="slide-content slide-insight">
          <p class="slide-overline">The Insight</p>
          <p class="slide-stat">73%</p>
          <p class="slide-stat-label">of Gen Z travelers say they want "authentic local experiences" — but the content they find is the same recycled top-10 lists.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="deck-slide reveal" style="background: #C4654A; color: #F0EDE5;">
        <div class="slide-content slide-solution">
          <p class="slide-overline" style="color: rgba(240,237,229,0.6);">The Solution</p>
          <h3>Three pillars for a new kind of travel platform.</h3>
          <div class="slide-pillars">
            <span>Perspective</span>
            <span>Story</span>
            <span>Community</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Motion Concept -->
  <section class="execution">
    <div class="section-label reveal">
      <span>Motion Concept</span>
      <span class="label-line"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="motion-grid">
      <div class="motion-description reveal">
        <h3>Social Animation</h3>
        <p>A film-grain photograph begins slightly zoomed in. Over 3 seconds, it slowly pulls back to reveal the full frame while the tagline types itself in Instrument Serif — letter by letter, with a subtle cursor. A light grain overlay drifts across the frame throughout. The result feels analog, human, and unhurried.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="motion-description reveal">
        <h3>Web Scroll Behavior</h3>
        <p>Content sections fade in with a 24px vertical translate and 700ms easing (expo out). Images move at 0.95x scroll speed for a gentle parallax. The navigation underline animates left-to-right on hover. On the landing page hero, the background image scales from 1.05 to 1.0 on load — creating a subtle "settling" effect.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Results -->
  <section class="results">
    <div class="section-label reveal">
      <span>Outcome</span>
      <span class="label-line"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="results-grid reveal-stagger">
      <div class="result reveal">
        <span class="result-number">340%</span>
        <span class="result-label">Increase in Instagram engagement over 3 months</span>
      </div>
      <div class="result reveal">
        <span class="result-number">28%</span>
        <span class="result-label">Increase in email open rates vs. previous campaigns</span>
      </div>
      <div class="result reveal">
        <span class="result-number">52%</span>
        <span class="result-label">Increase in time-on-site for the campaign landing page</span>
      </div>
      <div class="result reveal">
        <span class="result-number">2×</span>
        <span class="result-label">Featured in Communication Arts and It's Nice That</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="results-note reveal">
      <p>Campaign concept adopted for the brand's 2025 global refresh across all markets.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Next Project -->
  <section class="next-project reveal">
    <span class="next-label">Next Project</span>
    <a href="/work" class="next-link">View All Work →</a>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    padding: clamp(4rem, 10vh, 7rem) 0 2.5rem;
    max-width: 780px;
  }

  .hero-meta {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero-sub {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: #444;
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  .hero-image {
    margin: 0 calc(-1 * var(--page-padding));
    padding: 0 var(--page-padding);
  }

  .hero-placeholder {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 21/9;
    background: #1C1C1C;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .hero-tagline {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    color: #F0EDE5;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  /* Overview */
  .overview {
    padding: clamp(4rem, 8vh, 6rem) 0;
  }

  .overview-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
  }

  .overview-details {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem 2rem;
    align-content: start;
  }

  .detail-item h3 {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .detail-item p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .overview-text p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #333;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .overview-text em {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Problem & Insight */
  .problem-insight {
    padding: clamp(3rem, 6vh, 5rem) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .pi-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
  }

  .pi-block h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pi-block p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #444;
  }

  /* Strategy */
  .strategy {
    padding: clamp(3rem, 6vh, 5rem) 0;
  }

  .section-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .section-label span:first-child {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .label-line {
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--color-border);
  }

  .strategy-content {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .strategy-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .strategy-content p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #444;
  }

  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .pillar-num {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pillar h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .pillar p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  /* Tagline */
  .tagline-section {
    padding: clamp(4rem, 10vh, 7rem) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .tagline-section blockquote p {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  /* Campaign Messages */
  .messages {
    padding: clamp(3rem, 6vh, 5rem) 0;
  }

  .messages-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .message {
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .message p {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Visual System */
  .visual-system {
    padding: clamp(3rem, 6vh, 5rem) 0;
  }

  .system-intro {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .system-intro p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #444;
  }

  .palette {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .palette h3,
  .type-system h3,
  .image-direction h3 {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .swatches {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(6, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .swatch-color {
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .swatch-name {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .swatch-hex {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  /* Typography System */
  .type-system {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .type-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .type-sample {
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .type-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
